ISSUED BY COMPILED BY J. P. HEINTSCHEL, Vice-President S. PURSER PEEBLES CENTENNIAL PIPELINE LLC CENTENNIAL PIPELINE LLC 539 South Main Street 539 South Main Street Findlay, Ohio 45840 Findlay, Ohio 45840 (419) 421-4528 (419) 421-4048 spurserpeebl@marathonpetroleum.com
[C] GENERAL RULES & REGULATIONS
The General Rules & Regulations published herein apply in their entirety to the services covered by this Tariff, i.e., to the transportation and handling of Products between the origin and destinations named herein.
ITEM NO. 5 A List of Definitions Barrel Forty-two (42) United States Gallons at 60? F.
Batch A quantity of Products handled through Carrier's pipeline facilities as a unit.
Brand Shipment A Shipment of Products of uniform quality having the same specifications, which Shipment, Shipper desires separate identity and segregation from a Common Shipment so as to receive, as nearly as reasonably practicable, the same Products as delivered.
Carrier Refers to Centennial.
Common Shipment Any Shipment of Products that is not a Brand Shipment. Common Shipments will consist of commingled Products of similar quality, and which meet the specifications provided for in Item No. 125 of this Tariff, that are in effect at the time Product is tendered.
Force Majeure Event or Force Majeure Refers to, without limitation, acts of God; acts of a public enemy; fires; explosions; breakage of or accidents to machinery; equipment or lines of pipe; wars; earthquakes; storms; floods; extreme cold or freezing; extreme heat; washouts; necessity for compliance with any court order, law, regulation or ordinance promulgated by any governmental authority having jurisdiction; civil disturbances; strikes, lockouts or other industrial disturbances; the necessity for testing (as required by governmental authority or as deemed necessary by the testing party for safety of operation); inability of either party to obtain or delays in obtaining necessary materials, supplies, permits, or labor; inability to obtain, or delays in obtaining, appropriate rights-of-way; and any other causes, whether of the kind herein recited or not, which are not reasonably within the control of the party claiming suspension of its obligations.
Light Cycle Oil Includes a petroleum distillate that has the meaning as set forth in Item No. 125 of this Tariff.
Month Represents the period beginning at 12:00 a.m. (midnight) local Houston, Texas, time on the first day of a calendar month ending at 12:00 a.m. (midnight) local Houston, Texas, time on the first day of the next calendar month.
Product(s) Motor Fuels - Includes finished gasoline grades, naphtha, [N] natural gasoline, and raffinate subject to Item No. 125 of this Tariff.
Distillates - Includes jet fuel, diesel fuel, ULSD and petroleum distillates subject to Item No. 125 of this Tariff.
Shipments Includes both Brand Shipment and Common Shipment.
Shippers All parties who transport Product under the terms and conditions of this Tariff.
Tariff Means this FERC Tariff No. 14.1.0, supplements thereto and successive issues thereof.
ULSD Includes ultra low sulfur diesel subject to Item No. 125 of this tariff. A volume of ultra low sulfur diesel will be regraded to low sulfur diesel subject to Item No. 170 of this tariff.
ITEM NO. 20 Application of Rates for Intermediate Points For shipments accepted for transportation from any origin not named in this Tariff to a destination named in this Tariff, the rate for such shipment shall be the rate set forth in Item No. 180 from the closest named origin to such named destination to which such unnamed origin would be an intermediate point.
For shipments accepted for transportation from the origin named in this Tariff to any destination not named in this Tariff, the rate for such shipment shall be the rate set forth in Item No. 180 from the named origin to the closest named destination to which such unnamed destination would be an intermediate point.
For shipments accepted for transportation from an origin not named in this Tariff to a destination not named in this Tariff, the rate for such shipment shall be the rate specified in Item No. 180 from the closest named origin to the closest named destination to which such unnamed origin and unnamed destination are intermediate points.
Carrier will file a tariff publication applicable to the transportation movement within thirty (30) days of the start of the service if the intermediate point is to be used on a continuous basis for more than thirty (30) days.
ITEM NO. 50 Claims, Time for Filing As a condition precedent to recovery, claims must be made in writing to Carrier within nine (9) months after receipt of delivery of the Shipment, or in case of a failure to make delivery, then within nine (9) months after a reasonable time for delivery has elapsed. Suit against Carrier must be instituted by Shipper within two (2) years and one (1) day from the day when notice in writing is given by Carrier to the claimant that Carrier has disallowed the claim or any part or parts thereof specified in the notice.
Where claims for loss or damage are not filed or suits are not instituted thereon in accordance with the foregoing provisions and Carrier has not agreed to any extension of time, such claims will not be paid, and Carrier shall not be liable therefore. ITEM NO. 65 Delivery at Destination a. At Creal Springs, Illinois, Carrier will deliver Product into facilities of Enterprise TE caused to be furnished by Shipper.
b. At Dieterich, Illinois, Carrier will deliver Product into facilities of MPL caused to be furnished by Shipper.
ITEM NO. 70 Facilities Required at Origin & Destinations Shipments will be accepted for transportation hereunder only when:
(a) Shipper has provided the necessary facilities capable of delivering Products at the point of origin at pressures and at volumetric flow levels required by Carrier; and
(b) Shipper has provided the necessary facilities at destinations for receiving such Shipments without delay at pressures and at volumetric flow levels required by Carrier.
ITEM NO. 75 Identity of Shipments and Commingling Except for Brand Shipments, Product transported through Carrier's facilities for Shippers will be intermixed with substantially similar Products and shall be subject to changes in quality and other characteristics as may result from such intermixing. Except for Brand Shipments, Shipper shall not be entitled to receive the identical Product tendered by it to Carrier under this Tariff.
With respect to Brand Shipments, Carrier will reasonably endeavor to maintain the identity of Brand Shipments of Products.
ITEM NO. 80 Interface Responsibility Shipper(s) shall accept and be responsible for handling interface generated within or between Product movements from Creal Springs, IL to the Dieterich, IL - MPL connecting pipeline system.
ITEM NO. 90 Liability of Carrier Carrier shall not be liable for any loss or delay of, or damage to Products in or formerly in its possession caused by an act of God, public enemy, quarantine, authority of law, strike, riot, fire, flood, or act or default of Shipper, or for any other cause not due to the sole negligence of Carrier, whether similar or dissimilar to the causes herein enumerated; in such cases, except when Products involved in such loss are part of a Common Shipment, the owner of the Products shall stand the loss without any right to recourse against Carrier. In case the Product which is lost, damaged or delayed is part of a Common Shipment, the owner shall stand the loss from Carrier in the same proportion as the amount accepted for transportation and actually in Carrier's custody bears to the whole of the Common Shipment of all other Shippers participating in the Common Shipment from which such loss occurs. The owner of such Products shall be entitled to receive only such portion of its Common Shipment as is left after deducting the due proportion of the loss as determined above.
Carrier shall not be liable for discoloration, commingling, contamination or deterioration of Product transported unless such discoloration, commingling, contamination or deterioration is caused by the sole negligence of Carrier. Normal commingling which occurs between Batches may be divided as equitably as practicable among Shippers participating in the Batches causing the commingling.
ITEM NO. 95 Measurement and Deductions Product will be received and delivered on the basis of volume corrections for temperature from observed temperatures to temperatures on the basis of 60? F. Shipper shall have the privilege of being present or represented at time of measurement.
Except as provided in Item Nos. 80, 90 and 175 of Tariff, Carrier will be accountable for delivery at destination of one hundred percent (100%) of the original Shipment tender to the origins.
ITEM NO. 100 Minimum Consignment A minimum consignment of five thousand (5,000) Barrels of one Batch may be delivered to the destination, provided that delivery of such shipment does not result in reducing the continuing Shipment below ten thousand (10,000) Barrels for movements of an individual Product in Carrier's pipeline.
ITEM NO. 105 Minimum Shipment The minimum quantity of a Shipment which will be accepted at the point of origin by Carrier shall be fifty thousand (50,000) Barrels, provided, however:
(a) Common Shipments will be accepted by Carrier in a tender of not less than ten thousand (10,000) Barrels when the total of the tenders of a Common Shipment at one particular time will make a Batch of fifty thousand (50,000) Barrels or more of like characteristics at the origin;
(b) To the extent compatible with the efficient and economic use and operation of Carrier's facilities and pursuant to Shipper's request, Brand Shipments will be accepted and moved in a Batch of not less than fifty thousand (50,000) Barrels; and
(c) Shipper requesting a Brand Shipment shall be responsible for any commingling of Brand Shipments and Common Shipments resulting from the movement of the Brand Shipment Batch.
ITEM NO. 110 Payment of Transportation and Other Charges Carrier may require that all payments to Carrier for services pertaining to the transportation of Products under this Tariff be wire transferred in accordance with the instructions on the Carrier's invoice to Shipper and Carrier's published payment policy.
In the event Carrier determines that the financial condition of a Shipper or Shipper's guarantor (if any) is or has become impaired or unsatisfactory or Carrier determines it is necessary to obtain security from a Shipper, Carrier, upon notice to Shipper, will require any of the following prior to Carrier's delivery of Shipper's Products in Carrier's possession or prior to Carrier's acceptance of Shipper's Products: (1) prepayment of all charges by wire transfer and shall be held by the Carrier without interest accruing thereon until credited to the Shipper, (2) a letter of credit at Shipper's expense in favor of Carrier in an amount sufficient to ensure payment of all such charges and, in a form, and from an institution acceptable to Carrier, or (3) a guaranty in an amount sufficient to ensure payment of all such charges, and in a form, and from a third party acceptable to Carrier. In the event Shipper fails to comply with any such requirement on or before the date supplied in Carrier's notice to Shipper, Carrier shall not be obligated to provide Shipper access to Carrier's facilities or provide services pursuant to this tariff until such requirement is fully met.
Carrier shall have a lien on all Products in its possession belonging to Shipper to secure the payment of charges due by such Shipper and may withhold such Products from delivery until all of such unpaid charges shall have been paid. If such charges shall remain unpaid for ten (10) days after notice of readiness to deliver, or if Shipper has less than one hundred (100) Barrels of Products in Carrier's system which Shipper fails to remove after ten (10) days' notice from Carrier, Carrier shall have the right to sell such Products at public or private sale. Carrier may be a bidder and purchaser at such sale. From the proceeds of such sale, Carrier may pay itself all charges lawfully accruing and all expenses of such sale, and the balance remaining, if any, shall be held for whomsoever may be lawfully entitled thereto.
ITEM NO. 120 Product Disposition If No Facilities Provided at Destination In the event Shipper is unable to have Product delivered to it hereunder at a destination, as a result of Force Majeure or any other cause, Carrier shall reasonably cooperate with Shipper with respect to Shipper's disposal of such Product; provided, however, if Shipper fails to make provisions for such disposal within a reasonable time period given the circumstances, Carrier shall have the right, at Shipper's sole cost and expense and for Shipper's account, to dispose of any such Product at the best commercial price then reasonably available under existing circumstances in order to free any impacted pipeline capacity.
ITEM NO. 125 Product Acceptable Carrier reserves the right to reject any Shipments under this Tariff which would have a potential adverse effect on any Shipments, Carrier's facilities or otherwise disrupt the efficient use of Carrier's pipeline and associated facilities. Products tendered by Shipper pursuant to this Tariff for movement as part of a Common Shipment shall meet the specifications for the individual Product as set forth in Carrier's publication, "Centennial Fungible Specifications", which shall be modified or substituted from time to time and at any time to reflect Carrier's current published specifications for Product.
Light Cycle Oil tendered by Shipper pursuant to this Tariff for movement as part of a Brand Shipment shall meet the parameters as set forth in Centennial's publication, "General Characteristics of Light Cycle Oil", which shall be modified or substituted from time to time and at any time to reflect Carrier's current published parameters for Light Cycle Oil.
Subject to these General Rules & Regulations, Product as herein defined will be accepted for transportation at the origin at such time (i) as Products of similar quality and specifications are then being transported or (ii) Carrier is scheduling such Products for transportation from such origin to destinations in accordance with Carrier's sequence of pumping.
Common Shipments which will be accepted hereunder--unless prior approval is obtained from Carrier--are only those having an API Gravity of not less than 30? and not more than 90?, a vapor pressure of not more than 11 pounds per square inch absolute at the storing temperature, a temperature on receipt of not more than 100? F, viscosity not greater than 40 seconds Saybolt Universal and a color not darker than 2.5 ASTM.
Brand Shipments accepted hereunder--with prior approval from Carrier--are only those having an API Gravity of not less than 20? and not more than 90?, a vapor pressure of not more than 15 pounds per square inch absolute at the storing temperature, a temperature on receipt of not more than 100? F, viscosity not greater than 40 seconds Saybolt Universal and a color not darker than 4.0 ASTM.
Shippers requesting Product to be moved as a Brand Shipment will be required to furnish buffer material in reasonable amounts and quantities satisfactory to Carrier and Shipper for Shipments of Products. When Shipper is required under this Item No. 125 to provide buffer material for the Shipments of Products, Shipper will pay the same rate for the transportation of such buffer material as is the Transportation Charge applicable to the transportation of the Products the buffer material is being utilized to buffer. Shipments of Light Cycle Oil will be a Brand Shipment and require buffer material.
Shipper may be required by Carrier to inject oil-soluble corrosion inhibitors acceptable to Carrier in Products to be transported. Carrier, for corrosion protection, may inject corrosion inhibitors, and Products containing such inhibitors shall be accepted by Shipper or consignee of Shipper at destination.
ITEM NO. 130 Product Involved In Litigation or Encumbered Carrier shall have the right to reject any Products, when offered for transportation, that is involved in litigation, or the title of which is in dispute, or which is encumbered by lien or charge of any kind, and Carrier will require of Shipper satisfactory evidence of perfect and unencumbered title or satisfactory indemnity bond to protect Carrier against any and all losses.
ITEM NO. 135 Proration of Pipeline Capacity When quantities of Product greater than can be transported are offered to Carrier for Shipment through Carrier's facilities, Carrier shall allocate available transportation on an equitable basis to all Shippers pursuant to Centennial's Proration Policy, dated May 17, 2004, or any modifications thereto.
ITEM NO. 155 Tax Registration Shipper shall be required to provide Carrier with proof of registration with or tax exemption from the appropriate Federal and/or State tax authorities related to the collection and payment of fuels excise tax or other similar taxes, levies or assessments. Shipper shall further be required to immediately notify Carrier of any changes in their registration or tax exemption status. Any tax, levy, assessment or other charge imposed by such authority against Carrier as the result of such failure shall be collected by Carrier under the provisions of Item No. 110.
ITEM NO. 160 Tenders Carrier shall not be obligated to accept tenders for transportation of Products during any Month unless the Shipper shall have, on or before the fifth (5th) day of the preceding Month, notified the Carrier in any form of communication reasonably requested by Shipper which can be accommodated by Carrier, of the quantity of such Product which it desires to deliver at origin.
Notwithstanding the preceding paragraph, if requested by Carrier, Shipper shall furnish Carrier with a schedule of the expected deliveries of Products at origin and withdrawals at destination, setting forth Shipper's best estimate of daily rate of deliveries and withdrawals, and dates on which such deliveries and withdrawals shall commence. Acceptance of such schedule shall not constitute an obligation on the part of Carrier to meet such schedule.
ITEM NO. 165 Testing Shipper shall furnish Carrier with a certificate setting forth in detail specifications of each Shipment of Product offered for transportation under this Tariff, and Shipper shall be liable for any contamination or damage to other Products being transported, or to Carrier's pipeline or other facilities in the event Products tendered and shipped (i) include blending components that have not been approved by Carrier, or (ii) are substandard to the specifications stated in Shipper's certificate. Carrier may--but shall not be required to--sample and/or test any Shipment prior to acceptance or during receipt of Shipment, and in the event of variance between said certificate and Carrier's test, Carrier's test shall prevail as to the specifications of Products received.
ITEM NO. 170 Ultra Low Sulfur Diesel Re-grade of Product Two percent (2%) of the Volume of any Common Shipment of ULSD will be re-graded to low sulfur diesel so that the originating Shipper's inventory for the shipment will become ninety-eight percent (98%) ULSD and two percent (2%) low sulfur diesel. This re-grade will take place at the point of origin for the originating Shipper's inventory where the ULSD is received into Carrier's system
